Military Education Officer: The enemy has formed a simple
but solid formation near their camp. There is a sturdy
church nearby, and there are believers inside.

Military Education Officer: Prince Rex, how would you break
through this situation?
Young Rex: I think this is a very simple problem, teacher.

Military Education Officer: Please, do tell. This problem
has troubled many officers and is considered a difficult
question.

Young Rex: First, we will move our troops to lure the enemy
into the church. Getting them inside the church is the key
to the strategy.

Military Education Officer: Please continue.

Young Rex: Afterwards, we will surround the church with our
entire army. Since they have formed a simple formation, I
judge that the enemy does not have any reserve forces.

Military Education Officer: In that case, in a
disadvantageous situation... How would Prince Rex rescue the
hostages from this situation?
Young Rex: There are no hostages.

Young Rex: All imperial citizens are taught by my father,
who is a warrior dedicated to protecting the empire, to be
defenders of the empire.

Young Rex: My mother taught me that Terios believers are
taught to serve for the sake of the blessed empire, for the
gods.

Young Rex: As for the specific method, we will set fire to
the church and annihilate the enemy. The people in the
church will fulfill their duty as warriors and believers.

Young Rex: Everything is for the sake of the empire. The
believers should feel proud as they watch the enemy burn.

Young Rex: The strategy is to annihilate the enemy with
pride for the empire. As for the question, what were the
others troubled by?

This exchange was immediately reported to King Agnos and
Queen Leucos. Mother Leucos embraced Rex and repeatedly
apologized while crying. Father Agnos watched her without
saying anything.

Queen Leucos, for the first time, shouted and yelled at King
Agnos. She said, Your education has turned Rex into a
monster. King Agnos, for the first time, sincerely
apologized to his wife, Leucos.

It is an era where men have absolute power within the
household. Moreover, it is unthinkable for a king to
apologize to his wife. This shocking action caused Leucos to
uncontrollably burst into tears.

King Agnos' apology was not only for Rex. It was an apology
for the very essence of the royal bloodline. It was an
apology for the birth of a monster that cannot be resisted.

Rex, who witnessed the unusual scene of his father
apologizing, [reason unknown], felt ashamed of his own words
and apologized. He apologized to his respected father and
made his beloved mother cry.

Queen Leucos embraced Rex tightly and told him to become a
compassionate king. King Agnos, in a way of silent consent,
entrusted the emotional education to Leucos.

This incident robbed Rex of his confidence to become king.
He couldn't understand the reason why he made his mother
cry, or anything else for that matter. From this time on,
Rex stopped honestly expressing his thoughts.

Rex learned to become someone who can provide answers that
satisfy his mother, answers that satisfy his father, and
answers that satisfy his instructors. As a result, he became
a state of being [nothing]. Ultimately, this became a cage
for the monster that dwelled within his heart.

However, suppressing himself at such a young age came with a
cost. Rex's pain, anguish, and torment became food for the
monster within the cage.

Day by day, the monster grows by devouring its prey. In
order to stop it, one must erase oneself and rebuild the
cage. But this very action becomes the prey, causing the
monster to grow even further.

King Agnos was convinced that someday the cage would be
broken. Because there was a mighty monster within his own
heart as well. However, King Agnos had made a mistake in his
judgment.

King Agnos failed to realize that there was a monster far
more formidable than the one he possessed. He couldn't
perceive that this monster was continuing to grow.
